# Don't ship anything build-time — most Dockerfiles reinstall deps and rebuild.
# Excluding node_modules also avoids transient "invalid file request" failures
# when pnpm's symlink farm shifts under us mid-context-transfer.
#
# EXCEPTION: frontend vite apps are now built on the HOST (turbo-cached) and the
# thin app.Dockerfile just COPYs their pre-built output into nginx. So the dist/
# (and recipes' build/) dirs under apps/ MUST be in the build context. We keep
# the broad **/dist | **/build excludes (so packages/*/dist, service build dirs,
# etc. stay out of the context) and re-include only the app output dirs via `!`.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
!apps/*/dist
!apps/*/app/dist
!apps/recipes/app/build
**/.turbo
**/.next
**/.cache
**/.vite
**/coverage
**/test-results
**/playwright-report

# Local-only config and state
.env
.env.local
.git
.github
.claude
.data
backups
handoff
ARCHITECT-BRIEF.md
BUILD-LOG.md
REVIEW-REQUEST.md
REVIEW-FEEDBACK.md
SESSION-CHECKPOINT.md

# Editor / OS junk
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
